If you create a file .sln solutions and compile engine in its root folder, the file Urho3DAll.h is generated incorrectly.
For example in Cmd:
cmake_vs2015.bat D:\my\Urho3D\Urho3D-master -DURHO3D_OPENGL=1 -DURHO3D_SAMPLES=0
When you later compile your own game project, errors link occures. If in the file Urho3DAll.h comment out the line librevision.h,
```
...
#include <Urho3D/Urho2D/Urho2D.h>
#endif
#include <Urho3D/Urho3D.h>
#include <Urho3D/librevision.h> // error LNK2005
// #include <Urho3D/librevision.h> //no error

#include <Urho3D/DebugNew.h>

using namespace Urho3D;
```
then the compilation proceeds without errors.

```
SBVertex* vertices = (SBVertex*)vertexBuffer_->Lock(0, count * VERTICES_PER_SPRITE, true);
```
discard value is ignored in OpenGL.
```
void VertexBuffer::Unlock()
{
    ...
    case LOCK_SCRATCH:
        SetDataRange(lockScratchData_, lockStart_, lockCount_); // disacard = false
}
```
```
bool VertexBuffer::SetDataRange(const void* data, unsigned start, unsigned count, bool discard)
{
    ...
            if (!discard || start != 0) // condition always true
                glBufferSubData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, start * vertexSize_, count * vertexSize_, data);
            else
                glBufferData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, count * vertexSize_, data, dynamic_ ? GL_DYNAMIC_DRAW : GL_STATIC_DRAW);
}
```

Is it correct?

When load xml with InstantiateXML a CrowdAgent component is incorrect initialization because CrowdAgent component initialized (`agentCrowdId_ = crowdManager_->AddAgent(this, node_->GetPosition());`) **before** **node->SetTransform(position, rotation);** and node_ have position = Vector3(0,0,0).


May be make this )) :
`
void CrowdAgent::OnSceneSet(Scene* scene)
{
  AddAgentToCrowd(false, **false**);
}

and

int CrowdAgent::AddAgentToCrowd(bool force**, bool isCreated /*= true*/**)
{
    if (!node_ || !crowdManager_ || !crowdManager_->crowd_ || !**isCreated**)
        return -1;
`
